<br>
Some things that may have helped it go better:<br>
<br>
1.) Have non gating types bind in Halas.  That way if they fall into pits, they can run back into zone for a quick corpse summon.  While they get back, clerics , shamen, etc can junk buff.  We just seemed to keep getting killed by sending more into the pits.<br>
<br>
2.)  People who pull when told not to get one warning.  After that, they are disbanded from raid.<br>
<br>
3.)  Make sure everyone in our guild is comfortable using /loc.  Anyone 40+ should be ok getting to Permafrost entrance alone if they are late without a guide. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=singsang>SingSang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 822<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(10/28/02 12:40:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/Sing-B.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox October 26th, 12:30 Eastern</span><hr size=1> Agreed on all counts Ursi. Some of the undesired pulls came from CR's where the only way to get back was through Vox' room.<br>
<br>
The whole pit thing had perhaps 5 elements to it (including the CR aggos) that just kept plauging us. Next time I need to make sure that I have coffins in inventory that match up with whoever I have around to summon. Everything would have continued fairly quickly if we would have just had those in the pits suicide and summon them. With a 96% rez person around, I don't want to hear complains about having to suicide when they wound up in the pits from not following directions. I must have yelled about those pits 5 or 6 times before peeps fell into them. I'm going to have to raise it up next time.<br>
<br>
I figure I have one more shot at Vox before I have to choose between continuing to level vs. going full AA. I learned tons this time about things. I think I'm going to count on my signups a lot more next time, and pre-recruit pickup folks next time. Also, I'm probably going to do it as an evening raid as there are lots more peeps on to recruit from.<br>
<br>
I'll schedule it soon. I think I'll be able to find pickup raids with Naggy a bit more often, and Vox is up more, so I may shift the scheduled Naggy raid to Vox to try again (would move the time slightly). Basically, the white scale is the one I'm more worried about sources for, and I don't want to crowd the Exodus calendar.<br>
<br>
